<div class="station">Lauterbach Pier</div>
<div class="desc">
	Lauterbach Mole station is the dual‑gauge terminus (standard + 750 mm narrow
	gauge) at the edge of the Ruegischer Bodden. It functions as a “Zugbringer”
	(feeder train) for passengers transferring between the Regio‑Shuttle services
	and the historic steam‑hauled Rasender Roland.
